            . I am a <rs id="t18170917-313-viclabel1597" type="occupation">tailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-313-victim2154 t18170917-313-viclabel1597"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18170917-313-crimeloc1598">Gilbert-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-313-crimeloc1598" type="placeName" value="Gilbert-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-313-crimeloc1598" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-313-off1595 t18170917-313-crimeloc1598"></join>. I took the prisoner into my house when he was in great distress - He lived four months with me. On the 17th of September, between nine and ten o'clock at night, I went to bed, and left him undressing; he pulled off his breeches, put mine on, and then left the house; I missed the articles stated in the indictment. I was alarmed before ten o'clock-the shop-door was open, and I found him gone. He was taken on the Sunday.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170917-313-person2156">
                  NATHAN 
                  NATHAN
               <interp inst="t18170917-313-person2156" type="surname" value="NATHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-313-person2156" type="given" value="NATHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170917-313-person2156" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Cross-court, Russell-street. On the 17th of September, about half-past nine o'clock at night, the prisoner brought the things to my house, and wanted me to buy a coat; he put down eight or nine waistcoats, some finished and some not, and said he had to go to Liverpool, but had no money; and begged of me, for God's sake, to buy them, saying he made them himself.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
